$MidnightBSD: src/contrib/mksh/MIDNIGHTBSD-upgrade,v 1.2 2009/11/26 15:44:25 laffer1 Exp $

Directions for updating MKSH (work in progress)

1) Obtain the latest sources
2) Unpack sources.
3) Perform a test import (change version number as needed)
cvs -q -n import -m "Virgin import of MKSH R39" src/contrib/mksh MIROS vR39

4) if all goes well, 
cvs import -m "Virgin import of MKSH R39" src/contrib/mksh MIROS vR39

5) Check the Makefile in src/bin/mksh and the Build script for changes.
    Build.sh -M
6) update the dot file used for skel if needed.
